{
  "texts": [
    "In our prior research, we focused on understanding the needs related to existing services and improving the efficiency of service development through developers' proactive searches.",
    "In this study, we address two key challenges for achieving service personalization through a development-based approach: understanding the outline of new services demanded by users and discovering efficient development methods based on the extracted needs.This research aims to construct methodologies for efficiently developing services that meet user needs, starting from the users' active verbal input.",
    "By identifying the outlines of services users seek and discovering useful technologies for their development, it aims to facilitate the nuanced and efficient development of services that meet user demands.",
    "Our research group employs a dialogue-based needs extraction system employing virtual agents (VAs) and the Sharing Upcycling Cases with Context and Evaluation for Efficient Software Development (SUCCEED) system, as shown in prior studies [8,9].",
    "To capture various user service needs, this study proposes and implements a new dialogue-based needs extraction method for novel, undeveloped services not achieved in prior research."
  ]
}